    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TolE0347">
<l>iyaṟpeyar muṉṉart tantai muṟaivariṉ</l>
<l>mutaṟkaṇ meykeṭa vakara nilaiyu</l>
<l>meyyoḻit taṉkeṭu mavviyaṟ peyarē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>When proper names<note place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">Iyaṟpeyar.</foreign></note> [ending in <foreign xml:lang="ta">-ṉ</foreign>] are followed by the</l>
<l>relationship term <foreign xml:lang="ta">tantai</foreign> ' father '.</l>
<l>the initial [consonant] therein disappears, the sound <foreign xml:lang="ta">a</foreign> remains ;</l>
<l>that proper name, removing the consonant, loses the <foreign xml:lang="ta">aṉ.</foreign><note place="foot">i.e. <foreign xml:lang="ta">cāttaṉ + tantai &gt; 1. cāttu</foreign> (loss of <foreign xml:lang="ta">-aṉ) + antai</foreign> (loss of initial consonant ; <foreign xml:lang="ta">a</foreign> remains) &gt; 2. <foreign xml:lang="ta">cāttaṉtai</foreign> ' the father of <foreign xml:lang="ta">Cāttaṉ '.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
